channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: The Love We Share Seems to Go Nowhere - Hunter Biden's Delaware Trial - Day 4
George Clooney called White House to complain about Biden’s criticism of ICC and defend wife’s work: report
item.description: George Clooney reportedly called a top Biden aide to complain about the president’s critique of the ICC seeking an arrest warrant for Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.

item.title: Robert Wilkie to Newsmax: Biden Worldview Contradicts D-Day Message
item.description: The Obama-Biden worldview directly contradicts the message of D-Day and the U.S. military, former Veterans Affairs Secretary Robert Wilkie told Newsmax on Thursday.

item.title: More of Biden's Train Wreck Interview With David Muir: Hunter, Trump, Netanyahu, Insane Border Comment
Number of new gun owners since 2020 election surged to equal population of Florida: report
item.description: A recent report said that the number of new gun owners since the 2020 election reportedly equals 22.3 million people, or the population of Florida.

item.title: Biden Fires Back at Trump's 'Weak, Pathetic' Border Criticism
item.description: President Joe Biden responded to Donald Trump's criticism that his executive order on the border earlier this week was "weak and pathetic," asking rhetorically, "Is he describing himself?"

item.title: Sordid in the Court: Hallie Biden Describes Drug Use, How She Found Hunter's Gun
Netanyahu reportedly set to address Congress on July 24
item.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is set to address a joint meeting of the U.S. Congress on July 24, according to two sources familiar with the matter.

item.title: Rep. Jordan Sends for Florida Docs Case Prosecutor
item.description: House Judiciary Chair Jim Jordan sent a letter to a prosecutor on special counsel Jack Smith's team, inviting him to sit for an interview with the panel, which wants to inquire about his "unethical conduct" in the prosecution of Donald Trump in the classified documents case.

item.title: Lunden Roberts Reveals What a Lowlife Joe Biden Is
Elderly pro-life activist sentenced to prison after abortion clinic demonstration
item.description: Paula "Paulette" Harlow, a 75-year-old ailing Massachusetts woman, is hoping for a lighter punishment after her pro-life activism led to a two-year prison sentence.

item.title: Newsom Proposes New Budget That Defunds Police
item.description: The budget proposed by California Gov. Gavin Newsom, a Democrat, would cut police funding, since the state has a deficit of at least $45 billion, the Daily Mail reported.

item.title: Blaine Holt to Newsmax: Biden's D-Day Speech a 'Missed Opportunity'
item.description: Retired Air Force Brig. Gen. Blaine Holt criticized President Joe Biden's D-Day speech at Normandy appearing on Newsmax, labeling it a "missed opportunity" and advocating for a more robust message to honor the sacrifices of those who fought in World War II.
